I was told about this place from my Aunt. I had an opportunity to try the snapper escovitch fish at a party on 8/9/2020. When I tell you that fish was so flavorful and tasty.  I went today and ordered a bunch of things. I.e. rasta pasta, oxtail, curry goat, wings, callaloo rice, pumpkin rice and of course some snapper. The pasta, oxtail, curry goat and the carrots/peppers for the fish were 🔥. I mean head sweating hot 🔥.   I couldn't even share with my children. They were looking forward to the pasta and couldn't eat it. The sauce for the wings wasn't that bad but needless to say it was spicy.  A little pepper sauce should is ok but but someone clearly is putting too much in all the pots.  Portion sizes are small and lacks veggies and/or plantains.  Prices are a bit pricey.  I would definitely go back for fish since I can take off the onions, peppers and carrots but I will not order other meals.  I loved the fact that you can call ahead, place your order and pick up. In addition the food is separated.
